"v.筛，过滤 【英】 v.筛，过滤(to separate out by a sieve) 【同】 派生词: sifter (n.筛子) 【例】 Heavy soot sifted in through the open window. 无 【记】f=v 来自sieve；音：筛分它，细分它 sift (v.)  Old English siftan ""pass (something) through a sieve,"" from Proto-Germanic *sib- (cognates: Dutch ziften, Middle Low German sichten, German sichten ""to sift;"" see sieve (n.)). Intransitive sense ""to pass loosely or fall scatteredly"" is from 1590s. Metaphoric sense of ""look carefully through"" first recorded 1530s. Related: Sifted; sifting."
